            About Me
            I am a Master of Environmental Data Science student at UCSB, where I am learning to apply machine learning, statistics, and data visualization to my work in environmental science. My capstone uses decision-tree-based algorithms to explore variable importance from ecohydrologic model output. 
            
            
            Currently
            Data Scientist (Part-Time) @ RDN, Inc. 
            Graduate Student @ Bren School of Environmental Science & Management 
            Teaching Assistant @ UCSB Department of Economics
